subSubSection.paragraph:
Stethusa spuriella

differs from 

S. klimschi

in having a smaller body size; the bent apex of the median lobe (in lateral view; 

Figs. 
65­66

; 
50­51
); and a shorter spermatheca (

Figs. 
70

; 
57
).

Pronotum transverse, 1.2 times as wide as head, width 0.46­0.57 mm , length 0.36­0.44 mm , width to length ratio 1.3 ; glossy, with very weak isodiametric microsculpture (hardly visible at
70 x
); punctation as fine as on head but denser, distance between punctures equal to 1­2 times their diameter. Elytra much wider ( 0.59­0.73 mm ) and longer ( 0.43­0.57 mm ; measured from humeral angle) than pronotum (elytral length to pronotal length ratio 1.2 ), 1.3 times wider than long, surface glossy, with poorly visible (at
70 x
) microsculpture; punctation as on pronotum, slightly asperate.
